<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-13T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-13T21:00:00-05:00" n="409" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d409">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2670: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Forbes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-14T11:00:00+09:00">November 14, 1931—11
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 14—4:29
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>217. Your 266 [<hi rend="italic">226</hi>], November 13, 11 a.m. I have
                            carefully refrained from making any statement which could be construed
                            to indicate an expression of my Government’s attitude or of mine
                            regarding the new Japanese position.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Forbes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>